article.description: — CJ Hines scored 19 points to help Alabama State defeat Florida A&M 62-53 on Monday night.
article.headline: Hines leads Alabama State to 62-53 victory over Florida A&M
article.linkText: Hines leads Alabama State to 62-53 victory over Florida A&M
article.story: MONTGOMERY, Ala. -- — CJ Hines scored 19 points to help Alabama State defeat Florida A&M 62-53 on Monday night. Hines shot 7 for 17 (2 for 5 from 3-point range) and 3 of 5 from the free throw line for the Hornets (11-11, 6-3 Southwestern Athletic Conference). Antonio Madlock scored eight points. Ubong Okon had seven points and eight rebounds. Jalen Speer led the way for the Rattlers (4-16, 2-7) with 17 points. Shannon Grant added 10 points and seven rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
